  "prompt": "What are some useful online courses for management students?",
  "response": "There are numerous online courses that can be particularly beneficial for management students. Students should look for courses that are relevant to their specific interests and career goals within the field of management. Here are some recommendations:\n\n1. **Coursera:**\n   - **Business Foundations** by Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania\n   - **Foundations of Project Management** by Google\n   - **Organizational Analysis** by Stanford University\n   - **Strategic Leadership and Management** by University of Illinois\n   - **Leading People and Teams** by University of Michigan\n\n2. **edX:**\n   - **MicroMasters in Business Management** by IIMB (Indian Institute of Management Bangalore)\n   - **Project Management** by Rochester Institute of Technology\n   - **Entrepreneurship in Emerging Economies** by Harvard University\n   - **Culture-Driven Team Building** by University of Queensland\n\n3. **LinkedIn Learning:**\n   - **Leadership Foundations**\n   - **Strategic Planning Foundations**\n   - **Project Management Foundations**\n   - **Performance Management**\n   - **Finance for Non-Financial Managers**\n\n4. **Udemy:**\n   - **Management Skills \u2013 Learn How to Manage People**\n   - **The Complete Management Skills Certification Course**\n   - **Project Management: Master Project Management - PMP/PMI**\n   - **Team Leadership and Team Management 2023**\n\n5. **FutureLearn:**\n   - **Business Management: Principles of Management** by Open University\n   - **Decision Making: How to Choose the Right Problem to Solve** by University of Leeds\n   - **Management Essentials** by University of London\n\n6. **Skillshare:**\n   - **Management Skills: New Manager Training**\n   - **Leadership Skills for New Managers**\n   - **Business Development for Startups and Tech Companies**\n\n7. **Harvard Online Courses:**\n   - **Leadership Principles**\n   - **Negotiation Mastery**\n   - **Management Essentials**\n\n8. **MIT OpenCourseWare:**\n   - **Introduction to Operations Management**\n   - **Entrepreneurship and Business Planning**\n   - **Strategic Management**\n\nThese courses typically come with lectures, assignments, discussions, and sometimes peer interactions that can vastly improve the understanding and skills needed in management. It is advisable to read reviews and course outlines carefully to ensure they match your learning objectives and career aspirations.",
